items.name: Disease-Prediction-System
items.description: This project implements a Disease Prediction System using various machine learning algorithms to predict potential diseases based on user-provided symptoms. The system utilizes a Django web framework to provide a user-friendly interface for inputting symptoms and viewing the predicted disease.

items.name: Machine-Learning-API
items.description: This project aims to develop a machine learning API using Fast API web framework for predicting patients with Sepsis.

items.name: NASA-EOSDIS-Ecosystem-Classification
items.description: This project pioneers a PySpark-based machine learning framework for ecosystem health classification using atmospheric and environmental data. By seamlessly integrating PySpark with advanced machine learning algorithms, it analyzes diverse ecological features sourced from NASAs Earth Observing System Data and Information System (EOSDIS)

items.name: Spam-vs-Ham-Classifier
items.description: This project is an implementation of a machine learning classifier designed to distinguish between spam (unsolicited or unwanted messages) and ham (legitimate messages) in text data. Built using Python and popular machine learning libraries like scikit-learn, it provides a robust framework for classifying text data into spam or ham categories.

items.name: Deep-Dive-Into-AI-With-MLX-PyTorch
items.description: "Deep Dive into AI with MLX and PyTorch" is an educational initiative designed to help anyone interested in AI, specifically in machine learning and deep learning, using Apple's MLX and Meta's PyTorch frameworks.

items.name: SemiS-VFL
items.description: A Semi-supervised Machine Learning Framework for Vertical Federated Learning

items.name: GalaktaGlare
items.description: A broad, easy and fast framework for machine/deep learning in Go.

items.name: Random_Learning
items.description: Exploring some machine learning frameworks.

items.name: CardioGenAI
items.description: CardioGenAI: A Machine Learning-Based Framework for Re-Engineering Drugs for Reduced hERG Liability

items.name: Interactive-Design-Framework-User-Study
items.description: This repository contains all code that was used to conduct the user study based on a machine-learning-powered interactive design framework.

items.name: galaxies_datasets
items.description: Galaxies Datasets is a collection of ready-to-use extragalactic astronomy datasets for use with TensorFlow and other Machine Learning frameworks.

items.name: machine-learning
items.description: machine learning notes, assignments and framework tutorial

items.name: hitl
items.description: Code and documentation for Humans in the Loop (HITL), an LC Labs sponsored collaboration with metadata solutions provider AVP. The experiment explores a framework and considerations for integrating crowdsourcing and machine learning in ways that are ethical, engaging, and useful.

items.name: House-Price-Prediction-Webapp
items.description: House Price Prediction Webapp:  The House Price Prediction Webapp is an innovative tool that leverages machine learning to estimate house prices based on user-provided parameters, offering a seamless and insightful experience for individuals exploring real estate. Developed using the Flask web framework for Python

items.name: FLMMS
